text: after completing my degree in computer
science in 96 my first few jobs were in
startup companies working in a startup
there aren't as many people and the
roles are more fluid so it requires you
to develop an attitude that basically
everything is your job what i didn't
know at the time was this was preparing
me perfectly for a long-term career at
aws startup culture remains true today
through the amazon leadership principles
particularly ownership of bias for
action i joined amazon in 2007 as a
software development engineer on the
shopping cart team at that time we were
just a six-person team
the following year there was an internal
reorganization and we were moved into
what was then called the monitoring team
just as cloudwatch was being designed
and i've been with the team ever since
fast forward 13 years and today i'm the
general manager for cloudwatch based out
of dublin in ireland i lead engineering
and product management teams along with
engaging with all the various functions
like finance and hr to help to support
the team cloudwatch is an observability
solution allowing customers to collect
and store telemetry data such as metrics
logs and traces and subsequently
configure alarms and view graphs and
dashboards our customers include anybody
that uses an abs service they range from
small and medium enterprises to some of
the largest companies on earth
there have been so many accomplishments
on my journey in my dublin team we've
grown from six when i joined to more
than 100 today i'm particularly proud of
the fact that several of my team have
been with us for more than 10 years with
many of those growing their careers in
interesting ways and after all these
years it's still day one
